# crabcc-mcp tool catalog
# One tool per block. Format: name, description, required params, optional params, example.
# Auto-generated from schema.rs + mastodon.rs + memory.rs — keep in sync with source.

## sym
Find a symbol by exact name. Returns JSON array of {name, kind, signature, parent, file, line_start, line_end, visibility}.
- required: name
- optional: since (git revision)
- example: `sym name="Store::open" since="HEAD~10"`

## refs
Find every identifier reference to `name` across the indexed repo. Coarse — matches text equality on identifier nodes.
- required: name
- optional: mode (hits|files|summary|count), limit, if_changed, since, stream
- example: `refs name="UserId" mode="files" limit=20`

## callers
Find call sites of `name` — both bare (`foo()`) and method-receiver (`obj.foo()`) shapes.
- required: name
- optional: mode, limit, if_changed, since, stream
- example: `callers name="handleAuth" mode="count"`

## outline
All symbols in `file` ordered by line. Use parent field to reconstruct hierarchy.
- required: file
- example: `outline file="src/main.rs"`

## affected
Graph-derived change impact + targeted test selection. Returns {changed_files, changed_symbols, tests, runner, command}. Does NOT execute — run `command` yourself.
- optional: since, symbols, depth
- example: `affected since="HEAD~3" depth=3`

## test_context
Bundle every piece of context an LLM needs to generate a unit test for a symbol. Returns {symbol, callers, refs, outline, blast_radius}.
- required: name
- optional: file, max_callers, max_refs, blast_depth
- example: `test_context name="handleAuth" blast_depth=2`

## fuzzy
Fuzzy symbol-name search (Levenshtein distance 2). Use when the user might mistype or remember the name approximately.
- required: query
- example: `fuzzy query="Asseessment"`

## prefix
Prefix symbol-name search (case-insensitive starts-with).
- required: query
- example: `prefix query="getUser"`

## files
List indexed files. Token-cheap replacement for `ls -R` / `find -name`.
- optional: under, lang, ext, limit
- example: `files under="app/models" ext="rb" limit=100`

## index
Build a fresh full index (wipes existing). No params.

## refresh
Incremental refresh: mtime + sha256 diff vs stored.
- optional: delta (bool, include per-bucket file lists)
- example: `refresh delta=true`

## upgrade
Check GitHub for a newer crabcc release. Returns {installed, latest, delta, recommendations}.
- optional: apply, repo
- example: `upgrade apply=false`

## read
Outline-stub-aware file read. Cache key: (path, session_id) in memory.db. First read: full content. Subsequent: outline stub (~30x cheaper).
- required: path
- optional: mode (auto|full|stub|entropy), session_id, threshold
- example: `read path="src/main.rs" mode="entropy" threshold=2.5`

## write_file
Write a repo-relative file in full, then return a validation envelope: {wrote, validation: {parse_ok, parse_error, symbol_diff, broken_caller_files}}.
- required: path, content
- example: `write_file path="src/lib.rs" content="fn main() {}"`

## graph
Walk the call-graph sidecar (.crabcc/graph.json). BFS expansion of who calls (or is called by) `name`, capped at `depth`.
- required: name
- optional: dir (callers|callees), depth
- example: `graph name="Store::open" dir="callers" depth=2`

## graph_cycles
Find strongly-connected components of size ≥2 in the call-graph (mutual-recursion / cycle candidates). No params.

## graph_orphans
List symbols that call others but have no incoming callers. Dead-code triage starting point. No params.

## graph.blast_radius
Transitive callee explosion from a symbol.
- required: symbol
- optional: depth, kind
- example: `graph.blast_radius symbol="Store::open" depth=5`

## graph.why
Find the call path between two symbols.
- required: src, dst
- optional: max_depth
- example: `graph.why src="main" dst="Store::open" max_depth=8`

## graph.hot_symbols
Most-called symbols in the graph.
- optional: top, kind
- example: `graph.hot_symbols top=20 kind="function"`

## graph.importers
Files that import a given file, walked to `depth`.
- required: path
- optional: depth
- example: `graph.importers path="src/lib.rs" depth=3`

## ctx
Meta-tool: dispatch any other crabcc tool by name. Lets the agent compose calls dynamically.
- required: tool
- optional: args (object passed verbatim to the named tool)
- example: `ctx tool="sym" args={name="Foo"}`

## mastodon.post
Post a status to Mastodon. Agents use this to write reflections, release notes, or daily summaries. Returns {ok, id, url, created_at, content}. Safe to replay with the same idempotency_key.
- required: text
- optional: visibility (public|unlisted|private|direct, default=unlisted), spoiler_text, language, idempotency_key, bot, base_url
- auth: MASTODON_TOKEN env (or per-bot <BOT>_TOKEN)
- rate limit: 5 per 48h per token
- example: `mastodon.post text="v1.4.0 — outline streams. -71%." idempotency_key="release:1842" bot="crabcc"`

## mastodon.read
Read recent posts from a Mastodon timeline. Returns {ok, posts: [...], rate_limit: {...}}. Cached for 5 minutes.
- optional: timeline (home|public|tag, default=home), limit (1-40, default=20), hashtag, bot, base_url
- auth: MASTODON_TOKEN env (or per-bot <BOT>_TOKEN)
- rate limit: 5 per 48h per token
- example: `mastodon.read timeline="home" limit=10`

## mastodon.verify
Verify the Mastodon token and instance are reachable. Returns {ok, account: {id, username, display_name, acct, bot}, instance: {domain, title, version}}.
- optional: bot, base_url
- auth: MASTODON_TOKEN env (or per-bot <BOT>_TOKEN)
- rate limit: 5 per 48h per token
- example: `mastodon.verify bot="crabcc"`

## memory.init
Idempotent open-or-create for the memory store at <repo>/.crabcc/memory.db.
- optional: cwd

## memory.remember
Store one drawer (manual entry).
- required: source, body
- optional: cwd, wing, room, session_id
- example: `memory.remember source="finding-42" body="The Store::open bottleneck is SQLite pragmas" wing="dev"`

## memory.search
Search top-K drawers. Default mode is hybrid (BM25 + vector via RRF).
- required: query
- optional: cwd, limit, wing, room, mode (hybrid|lexical|vector)
- example: `memory.search query="Store::open bottleneck" limit=10 wing="dev"`

## memory.get
Fetch one drawer verbatim by id. Returns null if not found.
- required: id
- optional: cwd

## memory.list
List drawers (no similarity). Optional wing filter; ordered by id ASC.
- optional: cwd, wing, limit
- example: `memory.list wing="proj" limit=50`

## memory.delete
Delete drawers. Specify exactly one of: id, source, all.
- optional: cwd, id, source, all

## memory.forget
Delete drawers and run VACUUM to reclaim disk. Specify either {drawer} or {wing, before}.
- optional: cwd, drawer, wing, before

## memory.backup
Write a transactionally consistent snapshot of memory.db to `dest` using VACUUM INTO.
- required: dest
- optional: cwd

## memory.count
Drawer count for the store.
- optional: cwd

## memory.health
Health snapshot: Ok / Degraded / Down.
- optional: cwd

## memory.mine_project
Walk a repository and store one drawer per text file under wing="proj". Idempotent.
- optional: cwd, path, max_bytes, session_id

## memory.mine_sessions
Walk a JSONL directory of Claude Code transcripts and store one drawer per turn pair under wing="session". Idempotent.
- optional: cwd, dir, max_pair_bytes, session_id

## memory.remind_set
Schedule a reminder in the repo memory store. Pass either `due_at` (epoch seconds) or `delay` (human string: '1h30m', '2d').
- required: message
- optional: cwd, due_at, delay
- example: `memory.remind_set message="Check if PR #1182 merged" delay="2h"`

## memory.remind_poll
Atomically fetch all due reminders and mark them delivered. Returns [] when nothing is due.
- optional: cwd

## memory.remind_list
List reminders without marking them delivered.
- optional: cwd, include_delivered

## memory.remind_delete
Cancel a scheduled reminder by id. Returns {deleted: true|false}.
- optional: cwd, id

## _openapi
Return the embedded OpenAPI 3.1 description of this MCP server's tool surface (YAML). Dev mode only.

## _health
Liveness + capability probe. Returns server name, semver, protocol version, tool count. Dev mode only.
